stepTitle: Given the height, s, of a projectile after $$t$$ seconds is $$s(t)=-16t^2+80t$$, explain the meaning of $$s'(2)=16$$ in words.
answerLatex: After $$2$$ seconds, the projectile is increasing in height at a rate of $$16$$ feet per second.
